title: Perfect Behavior
creator: Donald Ogden Stewart
description: LibriVox recording of Perfect Behavior, by Donald Ogden Stewart. Read by Samanem. A humorous guide to manners and etiquette for ladies and gentlemen in a social "crises," published in 1922. (Introduction by Samanem) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: Humor; wit; satire; etiquette; literature; Librivox; audiobook
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: Truly excellent, if you are in to humour of manners.
reviews.reviewtitle: One of the funniest Librivox recordings I've listened to.
